title: VIRD: Autonomic Activity Monitoring System Using iPhone Viewer
title_en: VIRD: Autonomic Activity Monitoring System Using iPhone Viewer
abstract: 本研究は市販スマートフォンのビューアを用いて自律活動（バイタル情報）の遠隔監視を実現するシステムを提案している。 本システムはMEMSセンサ群と小型無線RF-ECGセンサを組み合わせてPCや次世代ネットワークとの連携を想定し、市販スマートフォンで生体データを受信・表示することを目的としており、無線RF-ECGの寸法40×35×7.2mm、質量12g、周波数2.4GHz、通信距離約20mといった工学的特徴を持つ。
abstract_en: This study proposes a system that uses a commercial smartphone viewer to perform remote monitoring of autonomic activity (vital information). This system combines MEMS sensors and a compact wireless RF-ECG sensor and is designed to receive and display biological data on a commercial smartphone while assuming integration with PCs and next-generation networks, with the RF-ECG sensor dimensions of 40×35×7.2mm, mass of 12g, frequency of 2.4GHz, and communication range of about 20m.
positioning_summary: 本研究は市販スマートフォンのビューアを用いた自律活動（バイタル情報）の遠隔監視の不足を埋めることを位置づけとしている。 本研究は携帯可能なMEMSセンサや無線RF-ECGからの生体データを市販スマートフォンで受信・表示する仕組みが不足している点を問題とし、遠隔モニタリングを必要とする利用者向けに受信・配信機能を提供する点で位置づけられている。
positioning_summary_en: This study is positioned to fill a gap in remote monitoring of autonomic activity using a commercial smartphone viewer. This study addresses the lack of mechanisms to receive and display biological data from portable MEMS sensors and wireless RF-ECG on commercial smartphones, targeting users who require remote monitoring.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は市販スマートフォンのビューアを用いて生体情報の遠隔受信と配信を可能にすることである。 本研究の目的は遠隔モニタリングを必要とする利用者に対して、MEMSセンサ群と小型無線RF-ECGセンサからのデータを市販スマートフォンで受信・表示する受信・配信機能を提供することである。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this study is to enable remote reception and distribution of biological information using a commercial smartphone viewer. The purpose of this study is to provide reception and distribution functions that allow data from MEMS sensor groups and a compact wireless RF-ECG sensor to be received and displayed on commercial smartphones for users who require remote monitoring.
method_summary: 本システムはスマートフォンビューアを中心にMEMSセンサ群と小型無線RF-ECGセンサを組み合わせてバイタル情報の受信・配信を行う構成を採用している。 本システムはPCや次世代ネットワーク（NGN/IMS）との連携を想定し、無線RF-ECGの寸法40×35×7.2mm、質量12g、周波数2.4GHz、通信距離約20mといった仕様を有するセンサ群を用いて市販スマートフォンで生体データを受信・表示する仕組みを実装している。
method_summary_en: This system adopts a configuration that centers on a smartphone viewer and combines MEMS sensor groups with a compact wireless RF-ECG sensor to receive and distribute vital information. This system implements a mechanism to receive and display biological data on commercial smartphones while assuming integration with PCs and next-generation networks (NGN/IMS), using sensor components that include an RF-ECG sensor with dimensions 40×35×7.2mm, mass 12g, frequency 2.4GHz, and communication range of about 20m.

Year: 2009
Abstract: This study proposes a system that uses a commercial smartphone viewer to perform remote monitoring of autonomic activity (vital information). This system combines MEMS sensors and a compact wireless RF-ECG sensor and is designed to receive and display biological data on a commercial smartphone while assuming integration with PCs and next-generation networks, with the RF-ECG sensor dimensions of 40×35×7.2mm, mass of 12g, frequency of 2.4GHz, and communication range of about 20m.
Positioning Summary: This study is positioned to fill a gap in remote monitoring of autonomic activity using a commercial smartphone viewer. This study addresses the lack of mechanisms to receive and display biological data from portable MEMS sensors and wireless RF-ECG on commercial smartphones, targeting users who require remote monitoring.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this study is to enable remote reception and distribution of biological information using a commercial smartphone viewer. The purpose of this study is to provide reception and distribution functions that allow data from MEMS sensor groups and a compact wireless RF-ECG sensor to be received and displayed on commercial smartphones for users who require remote monitoring.
Method Summary: This system adopts a configuration that centers on a smartphone viewer and combines MEMS sensor groups with a compact wireless RF-ECG sensor to receive and distribute vital information. This system implements a mechanism to receive and display biological data on commercial smartphones while assuming integration with PCs and next-generation networks (NGN/IMS), using sensor components that include an RF-ECG sensor with dimensions 40×35×7.2mm, mass 12g, frequency 2.4GHz, and communication range of about 20m.
